        "last_activity_date": 1454938507,
        "creation_date": 1435600510,
        "answer_count": 2,
        "title": "Pulling a field from another table in Hibernate",
        "body": "<p>I have two tables, which have a one-to-one relationship and look something like this:<\/p>\n\n<p><strong>OrderItem<\/strong><\/p>\n\n<pre><code>ID    data1   data2   data3\n1     a       b       c\n2     d       e       f\n3     g       h       i\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p><strong>DisputedItem<\/strong><\/p>\n\n<pre><code>ID    data4\n1     q\n3     r\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Is there a way to pull <code>data4<\/code> into my Hibernate model for OrderItem without having a separate DisputedItemModel? Preferably using annotations.<\/p>\n",
        "question_id": 31122400,
        "tags": [
            "java",
            "hibernate"
        ],
        "score": 5,
        "accepted_answer_id": 31122538,
        "is_answered": true,
        "view_count": 8571
    },
    "question_comments": [],
    "answers": [
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/0f75e7fb28ed0de5f8f3a3d40fa285a0?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
                "account_id": 1079377,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 1076789,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1076789/johnson-abraham",
                "reputation": 781,
                "display_name": "Johnson Abraham"
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 9,
            "is_accepted": true,
            "last_activity_date": 1435601012,
            "creation_date": 1435601012,
            "body": "<p>You can use Hibernate <code>@Formula<\/code> annotation, if you have annotation based mappings or <code>&lt;formula&gt;<\/code> tag if you are mapping by XML.<\/p>\n\n<p>What formula can do is help you extract a value by a query and map it to a field in your OrderItem domain model. This field can be from any table but the query thats used to map the property should return the indented field type.<\/p>\n\n<p>You can use following URL for reference <a href=\"http://gokhan.ozar.net/hibernate-derived-properties-formula-annotation/\" rel=\"noreferrer\">Hibernate Formula<\/a><\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 31122538,
            "question_id": 31122400
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://graph.facebook.com/10153024437984871/picture?type=large",
                "account_id": 5728679,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 4524908,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/4524908/seffy-golan",
                "reputation": 211,
                "display_name": "Seffy Golan"
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 5,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1454938507,
            "creation_date": 1452613236,
            "body": "<p>Yes, here is an example:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>@Table(name = \"table\")\npublic class c\n{\n    @Id\n    @Column(name = \"ID\")\n    private int Id;\n\n    @Formula(\"(select t.data from table t where t.ID = ID))\")\n    private String data;\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 34747851,
            "question_id": 31122400,
            "last_edit_date": 1454938507
        }
    ],
